Code quality fix - The diamond operator ("<>") should be used.
Code quality fix -  Class variable fields should not have public accessibility.
Code quality fix - Very confusing method names.
Code quality fix - Classes and methods that rely on the default system encoding should not be used.
Code quality fix - Resources should be closed.
Code quality fix - Synchronized classes Vector, Hashtable, Stack and StringBuffer should not be used.
Code quality fix - Array designators "[]" should be on the type, not the variable.
Code quality fix - super.finalize() should be called at the end of Object.finalize() implementations.
Code quality fix - Useless parentheses around expressions should be removed to prevent any misunderstanding.
Code quality fix - "entrySet()" should be iterated when both the key and value are needed.
Code quality fix - Parsing should be used to convert "Strings" to primitives.
Code quality fix - Declarations should use Java collection interfaces such as "List" rather than specific implementation.
Code quality fix - Methods named "equals" should override Object.equals(Object).
Code quality fix - Collection.isEmpty() should be used to test for emptiness.
Code quality fix - Utility classes should not have public constructors.
